---
description: Creating and updating files have up-to-date comments documented.
globs: src/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: true
---

- run @cursor_current_date_js to get the current date.
- The file itself starts with a block comment containing a short description of the file's overview. This block comments requires tag "@updatedAt" with today's system date in the YYYY-MM-DD format.

- When updating a file check for the block comment at the start of the file. If one is not there, add it.

- Creating or updating files are required to have its "@updatedAt" to be updated to today's date in the YYYY-MM-DD format.
